IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO CONDUCT A PRIVATE SCHOOL AND TO PROMOTE GENERAL EDUCATION IN THE PRIMARY, ELEMENTARY, SECONDARY, AND PRE-KINDERGARTEN LEVELS.

THE SCHOOL IS GENERALLY EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES UNDER THE PROVISIONS OF SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. HOWEVER, THE SCHOOL IS SUBJECT TO INCOME TAXES ON UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME AS DEFINED BY THE INTERAL REVENUE SERVICE. DURING THE YEAR ENDED AUGUST 31, 2022, THE SCHOOL HAD NO TAXABLE UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME AND ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION FOR INCOME TAXES IS REQUIRED IN THE ACCOMPANYING FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. MANAGEMENT EVALUATED THE SCHOOL'S TAX POSITIONS AND CONCLUDED THAT THE SCHOOL HAD TAKEN NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT REQUIRE ADJUSTMENT TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS TO COMPLY WITH THE PROVISIONS OF THIS GUIDANCE. THE SCHOOL FILES INCOME TAX RETURNS IN THE U.S. FEDERAL JURISDICTION. WITH FEW EXCEPTIONS, THE SCHOOL'S TAX RETURNS REMAIN OPEN FOR THREE YEARS FOR FEDERAL AND STATE EXAMINATION.

THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY THE SCHOOL'S INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM. THE FORM 990 IS THEN REVIEWED BY THE SCHOOL'S SENIOR MANAGEMENT. ONCE THE REVIEW BY SENIOR MANAGEMENT IS COMPLETE, THE FORM 990 IS THEN MADE AVAILABLE TO THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS PRIOR TO THE FILING OF THE FORM 990 WITH THE IRS.

EACH BOARD MEMBER IS REQUESTED TO REVIEW AND SIGN A STATEMENT ATTESTING TO ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. ANY CONFLICTS THAT ARE IDENTIFIED VIA THESE FORMS, OR OTHERWISE, ARE THOROUGHLY REVIEWED BY THE GOVERNANCE COMMITTEE, WITH BOARD MEMBERS BEING ASKED TO ABSTAIN FROM BOARD VOTES RELATED DIRECTLY TO CONFLICTS OF THEIRS.

HEAD OF SCHOOL COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED AND APPROVED BY THE HEAD SUPPORT EVALUATION SUBCOMMITTEE AND IS DOCUMENTED IN THE COMMITTEE'S MINUTES. ADDITIONALLY, CHANGES TO SALARY AND BENEFITS (IF ANY) ARE REVIEWED AND APPROVED IN THE BUDGET REVIEW PROCESS AND THESE NOTES ARE PRESENTED TO THE BOARD. ANALYSIS IS CONDUCTED OF PEER SCHOOLS AS IDENTIFIED IN THE STATE OF THE SCHOOL REPORT, ALONG WITH AIMS MEMBER SCHOOLS AND SIMILARY-SIZED NAIS SCHOOLS. THE INCREASE IS INTENDED TO PLACE THE HEAD'S SALARY APPROACHING A PERCENTAGE NEAR THE AVERAGE OF THE PEER SCHOOLS.
